Pre-Game Insights: The Orioles will provide tickets to the families of three young Orioles fans who passed away from cancer in the last year.
The Orioles Charitable Foundation will make a $5,000 donation to the Casey Cares Foundation.
The Orioles will donate tickets to the families of children who are currently being treated for cancer and who participated in the 2024 Maryland Trek.
Hyundai will make a donation to Johns Hopkins Pediatrics before the game.
The Camden Franks will compete against one another live at Oriole Park.
The first 20,000 fans ages 15 and over will receive an ORIOLES T-SHIRT HOODIE, presented by Ledo Pizza.
Post-Match Reflections: Aaron Judge expressed pride in the team's resilience after the comeback win.
The coach highlighted the victory as a pivotal moment in their playoff push.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The game will feature a ceremonial first pitch from a pediatric cancer patient from Hyundai Hope on Wheels.
The Baltimore Symphony Orchestra will perform the national anthem from behind home plate.
James McCann will visit NICU nurses and families at MedStar Franklin Square Medical Center.
The Orioles Family Program will partner with the Orioles and Prom Series to provide homecoming dresses to local foster girls.

The Orioles will wear their City Connect jerseys at each Friday home game throughout the regular season, and this year, every City Connect Friday will be dedicated to Harlem Park Elementary Middle School.
